data.enText: to prove that sth is wrong
to refute an argument/a theory, etc.
to say that sth is not true or fair

data.chText: 谁要是表示她不在行，她都予以反驳。
data.enText: She refutes any suggestion that she behaved unprofessionally.

data.chText: 对过去所坚持的观点的否定
data.enText: a refutation of previously held views

simple_means.memory_skill: re 反 + fut〔= fus〕流，泻；融化 + e → 反流 → 反驳

tr: prove to be false or incorrect
overthrow by argument, evidence, or proof
example: The speaker refuted his opponent's arguments

value.def: If you refute an argument, accusation, or theory, you prove that it is wrong or untrue.

example.ex: It was the kind of rumour that it is impossible to refute.
example.tran: 这是那种让人根本没法批驳的谣言。

value.tran: 驳倒，驳斥，批驳（观点、指责或理论）

value.def: If you refute an argument or accusation, you say that it is not true.

example.ex: Isabelle is quick to refute any suggestion of intellectual snobbery.
example.tran: 伊莎贝尔对于任何关于她恃才傲物的暗示都迅速予以否认。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to pour, to melt 流, 泻；融化
rootsaffixes.title: fus

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 流到一起 → 使混乱
dif 分开 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 分流 → 散播
ef 出 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 流出；吐露
ef 出 + fus 流，泻；融化 + ive …的 →〔感情〕流出的 → 溢出的
in 进入 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 流进去 → 注入
pro 向前 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 不断向前涌出的 → 丰富的
re 相反 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 向回流 → 拒绝
re 反 + fut〔= fus〕流，泻；融化 + e → 反流 → 反驳
suf 下 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e → 在下面流〔得到处都是〕→ 充满
trans 横过 + fus 流，泻；融化 + e →〔让血〕穿过 → 输血
